<paragraph id="99BF294237B5696ABBA9F027C6A3B5A3" pageId="407" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis id="71B6E2C6CDBE7C117F19EA27CAC0F4B0" bold="true" pageId="407" pageNumber="408">USA</emphasis>
: AZ, NM - Mexico
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D961A3F3F0730D9E3A35C49C6A43D86D" pageId="407" pageNumber="408" type="note">
<paragraph id="6B7319C3BB57781B7CE9E4E008E06139" pageId="407" pageNumber="408">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="457D33FAFBD4A713E9A45DA64E27908F" pageId="407" pageNumber="408">
This taxon has been listed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="6C14AAF6A553A4747669A42D3DDC8098" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="407" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aratum">
<emphasis id="F306351F188256EE2905FEB0426B248F" italics="true" pageId="407" pageNumber="408">Bembidion aratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LeConte) by Erwin (1982b: 479) but according to Maddison (2012: 535) it represents a distinct species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
